The paper describes a semantic model for scientific argumentation and annotation in biomedical publications, which involves natural language processing, data modeling, and knowledge representation. This suggests that the paper could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the NLP aspect, Databases (cs.DB) for the data modeling aspect, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) for the citation network construction aspect, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) for the natural language processing aspect, and Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the knowledge representation aspect.
